cs.CR, cs.NI, cs.DC, cs.MM, cs.SD 

This paper discusses the development of a censorship-resistant infrastructure, which involves network-based censorship mechanisms and circumvention systems. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security), followed by cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) and cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). The paper also involves the use of VoIP connections and acoustic signals, which could fall under cs.MM (Multimedia) and cs.SD (Sound and Music Computing).
